^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let me discuss the 3@C bid and the way some people show a "bust" hand as responder over 2@C. There are a few alternatives. One is to not worry about showing a bust hand. The other is to play that 2@D over 2@C promises at least 1 ace or king and with no aces or kings responder bids 2@H. The problem I have with that approach is that sometimes wrong sides the contract when the 2@C bidder has hearts. so I don't particularly care for that approach although it is reasonably popular.|
